(42, 2, 14, 58, 13, 20, 21, 'peace, good will toward men', 'Connection of Peace and Glory', 'Both passages emphasize the themes of peace and glory. Luke 2:14 speaks of ''peace, good will toward men,'' while Hebrews 13:20 refers to ''the God of peace'' and concludes with a call for glory to Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
