(42, 2, 15, 40, 2, 1, 2, 'Bethlehem', 'Journey to Bethlehem', 'This connection highlights the journey to Bethlehem, where both the shepherds and the wise men seek the newborn Jesus. The shepherds are prompted by the angels, while the wise men are guided by a star, emphasizing the significance of Bethlehem as the birthplace of Jesus.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 15, 60, 3, 22, 22, 'angels were gone away from them', 'Angels and Divine Revelation', 'This connection highlights the role of angels in revealing God''s plans. In Luke, the angels announce the birth of Christ, while in 1 Peter, it emphasizes Christ''s authority over angels.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 15, 2, 3, 3, 3, 'see this thing which is come to pass', 'Divine Revelation and Response', 'This connection highlights the theme of responding to divine revelation. In both passages, characters are prompted to ''see'' significant events that God has made known to them.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 15, 40, 2, 9, 11, 'see this thing which is come to pass', 'Journey to Worship the Child', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking and finding the young child, as both passages describe individuals responding to divine revelation. The shepherds in Luke go to Bethlehem to see what the Lord has made known, while the wise men in Matthew follow the star to worship the child.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 15, 12, 2, 1, 1, 'it came to pass', 'Heavenly Ascension and Revelation', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine revelation leading to significant events. Both passages emphasize the moment when the Lord communicates important truths, prompting a journey towards a pivotal location.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 15, 12, 2, 11, 11, NULL, 'Divine Revelation and Response', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine revelation leading to human response. In both passages, significant events occur as individuals are prompted to act upon what has been revealed to them.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 15, 19, 111, 2, 2, 'see this thing which is come to pass', 'Divine Revelation and Response', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking out the works of the Lord. In both passages, there is an emphasis on recognizing and responding to God''s actions, as the shepherds seek to witness the divine event announced by the angels.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
