(42, 2, 16, 42, 19, 32, 32, NULL, 'Finding as a Thematic Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of finding. In Luke 2:16, the shepherds find Mary, Joseph, and the babe, while in Luke 19:32, the disciples find things as Jesus had said.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 16, 42, 1, 39, 39, 'with haste', 'Haste in Mary''s Journey', 'Both passages emphasize the urgency of Mary''s actions. In Luke 1:39, she goes ''with haste'' to visit, while in Luke 2:16, the shepherds come ''with haste'' to find her and the babe.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 16, 42, 22, 13, 13, NULL, 'Finding and Preparation', 'This connection highlights the theme of discovery and readiness. In both passages, the characters find what they are looking for and prepare accordingly, emphasizing the importance of following instructions and fulfilling roles.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 16, 21, 9, 10, 10, 'found Mary, and Joseph, and the babe', 'Work and Urgency in Life', 'This connection highlights the urgency of action in both passages. In Luke, the shepherds act quickly to find the babe, while Ecclesiastes emphasizes doing work with might before death limits opportunities.', 'theme', 0.307, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
