(42, 2, 17, 19, 71, 17, 18, 'made known abroad the saying', 'Proclamation of God''s Works', 'This connection highlights the act of declaring God''s works. Both passages emphasize the importance of sharing the wondrous deeds of God across generations.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 17, 39, 3, 16, 16, 'made known abroad the saying', 'Proclamation of God''s Message', 'This connection highlights the act of making known God''s message. Both passages emphasize the importance of speaking about the Lord and sharing what has been revealed.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 17, 42, 2, 38, 38, 'made known abroad the saying', 'Proclamation of Redemption', 'This connection highlights the theme of proclaiming the news of Jesus. Both passages emphasize sharing the message of redemption, with the shepherds making it known and Anna speaking of him to those looking for redemption.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 17, 43, 1, 41, 46, 'made known abroad the saying', 'Announcement of Finding the Messiah', 'This connection highlights the theme of proclaiming the discovery of Jesus as the Messiah. Both passages emphasize the act of sharing the news about Jesus, first by the shepherds and then by the disciples.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 17, 43, 4, 28, 29, 'made known abroad the saying', 'Proclamation of Christ''s Identity', 'This connection highlights the theme of proclaiming the identity of Jesus. In both passages, individuals share their experiences of encountering Christ, emphasizing the importance of making known the truth about Him.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 18, 42, 1, 65, 66, 'all they that heard it wondered', 'Wonder and Fear in Response', 'Both passages emphasize the reaction of those who heard the news about the miraculous events surrounding Jesus'' birth. In Luke 2:18, the shepherds'' message evokes wonder, while in Luke 1:65-66, the news inspires fear and contemplation about the child''s significance.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 18, 42, 2, 33, 33, 'wondered at those things', 'Wonder and Marvel in Luke', 'Both passages emphasize the reaction of wonder and amazement. The shepherds and Joseph and Mary both respond with marvel at the revelations concerning Jesus.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 18, 42, 4, 36, 36, 'wondered at those things', 'Response to Authority and Wonder', 'Both passages emphasize the reaction of amazement from those who witness extraordinary events. In Luke 2:18, the shepherds'' message evokes wonder, while in Luke 4:36, Jesus'' authority over unclean spirits similarly astonishes the crowd.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
